#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:6
msgid ""
"This page contains configuration instructions for advanced IPT users only.  "
"Datasets published with a different license to those included by GBIF cannot "
"be published to GBIF, or registered to GBIF."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:8
msgid "We recommend publishing a metadata-only dataset instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:11
msgid ""
"Since IPT v2.2 the IPT ships with 3 machine readable licenses to choose from "
"when applying a license to your resource:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:13
msgid "Public Domain (CC0 1.0, technically a waiver)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:14
msgid "Creative Commons Attribution (CC-BY 4.0)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:15
msgid "Creative Commons Attribution Non Commercial (CC-BY-NC 4.0)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:17
msgid ""
"Each license has a default rights statement associated to it that gets shown "
"to users. For example, if the publisher chooses to apply CC-BY to their "
"resource, this rights statement shown to users is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:20
msgid ""
"This work is licensed under a https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/"
"legalcode[Creative Commons Attribution (CC-BY) 4.0 License]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:22
msgid ""
"The list of licenses and their rights statements can be modified, however, "
"which is useful for communities that need to apply different licenses to "
"their resources, or that want to include additional usage instructions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:24
msgid ""
"The steps below explain how to configure the IPT with another license to "
"choose from."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:28
msgid ""
"Locate the licenses.properties file e.g. /tomcat7/webapps/ipt/WEB-INF/"
"classes/org/gbif/metadata/eml/licenses.properties. Open the file in a text "
"editor, and do the following:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:30
msgid ""
"Add a new property defining the license name using the following format:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:35
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"license.name.<prefix>=Name\n"
"# For example:\n"
"license.name.odcby=Open Data Commons Attribution License (ODC-By) 1.0\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:38
msgid ""
"Add a new property defining the license rights statement using the following "
"format:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:43
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"license.text.<prefix>=Text\n"
"# For example:\n"
"license.text.odcby=This work is licensed under a <a href=\"http://www.opendatacommons.org/licenses/by/1.0\">Open Data Commons Attribution License (ODC-By) 1.0</a>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:46 en/modules/ROOT/pages/user-id.adoc:36
msgid "Double check"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:47
msgid "the _prefix_ of both keys matches,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:48
msgid ""
"an HTML anchor defining the license name and URL is included in the text "
"since this is what makes the license machine readable,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:49
msgid ""
"the name used in the HTML anchor is the same as name used in the name "
"property above."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:50
msgid ""
"Backup the licenses.properties file, since it will get overwritten the next "
"time you upgrade your IPT"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/license.adoc:50 en/modules/ROOT/pages/user-id.adoc:39
msgid ""
"Restart your servlet container (e.g. Tomcat) so that the new configuration "
"takes effect"
msgstr ""
